cs.DC, cs.CC, cs.DS, cs.SY, cs.CR 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - This paper deals with caching policies for cloud-based systems, which are inherently distributed and parallel. 
2. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper discusses the cost of a cloud-based system and proposes a caching policy that minimizes this cost, which can be seen as a computational complexity problem. 
3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The caching policy proposed in the paper is based on the frequency of consumption of an item, which is a data structure problem. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with designing and evaluating a caching policy for a cloud-based system, which can be seen as a control problem. 
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - Although not the main focus of the paper, the use of cloud storage services such as Amazon S3 as a cache raises security and privacy concerns, which can be relevant to the cs.CR sub-category.
